6:
All right, direct our sails towards the
starboard!
9:
B-but miss... that ain't the direction
of Paradise Isle.
12:
What, you don't believe in your
captain?!
16:
The captain and her crew must be
one in body and spirit! Our path lies
in our sight!
20:
What I'm trying to say is... go where
you're supposed to go! I'll go
wherever you take me!
24:
A simple "Okay, sounds good!"
would've worked just as well...
28:
I've got a good feeling about this
trip... This time, I WILL find Eden!
34: I'm gonna go search for Eden!
39:
I feel like I say this a lot, but... What
are you talking about?
43:
To be honest, I forgot about it
myself. You see, there's a certain
place I'm lookin' for.
47:
A utopia that can only be reached
by the Umamusume who wields the
ultimate power... The Eden described
in the Book of Secrets.
55:
Yup, found it in the academy fields.
They even wrote, "Yours truly, the
Book of Secrets" in their message to
me!
59:
You should've been there... My
sixteen-pound ball split the earth in
two... 'Twas a sight to behold.
63:
In terms of bowling though, it was a
pretty normal feat.
69: I'd love to search for Eden with you.
73:
Oho, now we're talking! Good to see
that the spirit of adventure flows
through you!
77:
Yeah! So what if we don't have any
clues? We'll search the whole
universe until we find it! Isn't that
right, my fellow Golgol Investigators?!
91:
The voyage was long and arduous.
Yet despite the attacks by pirates
and ferocious krakens, we continued
to sail on into the eye of the storm...
94:
Well, we did hijack a pirate ship to
get here, but the rest of that is
nonsense.
99:
But at long last, we have reached
our destination—Paradise Isle!
111:
Oh yeeeah! Forgot about that.
Guess I had too much fun on that
boat ride. My baaad!
114:
But wait... I know Eden smells like my
grandpappy's house, so... Maybe
that boat ride was the right call...
117:
No wait, I feel like it also smells like
your socks after a long day of work...
Like my papa's fishing boat!
120:
Sounds like you just wanted to ride a
boat...
124:
Not really. No one in my family sails
anyway.
127:
Now, let me hear ya shout! Our
journey up until now has been
nothing but a mere prelude! We've
cast our nets, so let's see what we
reel in!
140:
What the hell?! We haven't found a
clue about Eden! I thought you'd
show me some SKILLS here!
144:
Speaking of skills, didja know there's
something called a skilfish? Unlike
the oilfish, it's perfectly edible if
eaten in moderation.
151:
Well, who knows what exists in this
world? Maybe Eden and Skilfish exist
here, and maybe they don't.
155: You haven't even tried finding either!
159:
But how could I possibly begin my
search when my heart and legs are
screaming for more fun—MORE
THRILLS!
162:
Is this the end of the Golgol
Investigators' quest for Eden?!
165:
Ah well. This was fun. I guess we can
stop here—
173:
Oho... Is that fire I see in your eyes?
Looks like you're not ready to throw
in the towel yet!
177:
I am not. I want to keep having fun
with you.
181:
Sounds good to me! You want fun?
I'll show you FUN!
186:
Huh? What's this poster doing here...
Looks like it's for a triathlon.
195:
"An invitation to Paradise, the
island's premier gourmet
experience?!" Th-that means...
200:
We've found it! This is our ticket to
EDEN!
208:
Big deal! All I know is we've got a
race to win!
212:
You sure about this? This is a pretty
hard competition to just jump into
spontaneously.
216:
Aren't you forgetting something?
You're looking at Golshi—an
Umamusume strong enough to find
Eden!
220:
Doesn't matter what kinda race it
is—I'm winning!
225:
Our athletes are coming into view!
They're clearly worn out, but we're in
the final stretch! Will they make it?!
228:
Look at that run! Not even an inkling
of fatigue can be felt from her! It's
like she warped straight to the front!
Will she maintain her lead?!
241:
Spin-turn and wow! My first-place
pose!
244:
What didja think of that, Stella? How
was my super awesome running?
252:
Yeah, well, I'm still not at my peak.
Until the day I reach Eden...
256:
I will work hard to become... the
world's best shogi player!
